When generating git commit messages:
- Follow Conventional Commits specification (feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, etc.)
- Use the emoji from the cz-emoji package mapping for the commit type
- Format: <emoji> <type>(<scope>): <short description>
- Subject line: terse and direct, no filler words, no flowery language
- Body (optional): explain why and how, but each line must be max 100 characters
- Wrap body lines at 100 chars — never exceed it